parts.text: The decision to make "Client Details - AEC - Transparency Website" publicly available, with no applicable exemptions, directly supports core right-leaning tenets by actively combating government overreach. This unhindered transparency empowers market freedom by enabling citizens and businesses to scrutinize government interactions with its "clients," fostering a more level playing field and reducing opportunities for cronyism or preferential treatment that distort the market. Furthermore, this commitment to openness serves the national interest by enhancing public accountability, ensuring fiscal responsibility, and bolstering the principle of limited government by preventing secrecy and promoting informed public oversight of government operations.
